&lt;ul>
&lt;li>This recipe makes 2 8-inch pies or 1 9-inch pie.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>1.5 cups of graham crackers&lt;/li>
&lt;li>6 tbsp butter&lt;/li>
&lt;li>1/3 cup sugar&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Ingredients for &lt;a href="https://mowery.dev/recipes/lime_mousse/">Lime Mousse&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="instructions">Instructions&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Food process the graham crackers into a fine crumble, then dump the crumbs into a mixing bowl&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Food process the butter and sugar together, then add them to the graham crackers&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Pat the mixture into a pie tin&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Follow the recipe for the lime mousse, then pour the result over the pie tin&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Let set in the freezer&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h1 id="images">Images&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="../images/lime_mousse_pie.webp" alt="Lime Mousse Pie">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Plum Cake (Pflaumenkuchen)</title><link>https://mowery.dev/recipes/plum_cake/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mowery.dev/recipes/plum_cake/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="notes">Notes:&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>For historical reasons this is named &amp;ldquo;Plum Cake&amp;rdquo; but it is actually a pie.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>This is our version of Pflaumenkuchen.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="wet-ingredients">Wet ingredients&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>1 stick butter (1/2 cup)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>1 egg&lt;/li>
&lt;li>2/3c sugar&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="dry-ingredients">Dry ingredients&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>1 1/2c flour&lt;/li>
&lt;li>1/2 Tbsp baking powder&lt;/li>
&lt;li>1 pinch salt&lt;/li>
&lt;li>1/2 cinnamon&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="plums">Plums&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>1.5 lbs italian plums, halved&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="the-topping">The topping&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>1 tsp cinnamon&lt;/li>
&lt;li>1/4c hazelnuts&lt;/li>
&lt;li>(After baking, optional) 1 Tbsp cane sugar&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="instructions">Instructions&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Preheat oven to 375*F.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Grease pie tin with the butter stick.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Process all the wet ingredients (including sugar) in a food processor.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Mix all the dry ingredients in a bowl.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir them together to create a dough.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Press the dough into the pie tin; optionally stick it in the fridge to chill.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Halve all the plums, then press them into the dough, arranging them skin side down but slightly sideways and overlapping (see image).&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Use a food processor to chop up all the hazelnuts.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Mix the cinnamon into the chopped hazelnuts, then sprinkle it over the plums.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Bake for 30-45 minutes, until crust is golden and/or plums begin to bubble.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Sprinkle a bit of sugar over the plums.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="../images/plum_cake_1.webp" alt="Fondue">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Waffles</title><link>https://mowery.dev/recipes/waffles/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mowery.dev/recipes/waffles/</guid><description>&lt;p>Laura&amp;rsquo;s waffle recipe, stolen from ancestors.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The portions here are for 2 people to eat a large breakfast.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>If feeding more people double or triple the amounts below.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="equipment">Equipment&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Blender&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Waffle iron that makes hearts&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="ingredients">Ingredients&lt;/h2>
&lt;script defer>
 function onMathJsLoad() {
 const servingFactorElement = document.getElementById("servingFactor");
 if (!servingFactorElement) {
 return;
 }
 math.config({
 number: 'Fraction',
 });
 const intendedServingFactor = servingFactorElement.valueAsNumber;
 const elementsAndOriginalValues =
 Array.from(document.querySelectorAll("span.unit"))
 .map(unitElement => {
 return {
 unitElement,
 quantity: math.fraction(unitElement.textContent),
 }
 })

 servingFactorElement.addEventListener("change", () => {
 const newServingFactor = servingFactorElement.valueAsNumber;
 const servingFactor = math.fraction(newServingFactor, intendedServingFactor);
 const unitElements = document.querySelectorAll("span.unit");
 for (const { unitElement, quantity } of elementsAndOriginalValues) {
 const scaledUnit = math.multiply(quantity, servingFactor);
 let formattedScaledUnit = math.format(scaledUnit).replace(/^(.*)\/1$/, "$1");
 unitElement.textContent = formattedScaledUnit;
 }
 });
 }
&lt;/script>
&lt;script defer onload="onMathJsLoad()" src="https://unpkg.com/mathjs@11.5.0/lib/browser/math.js">&lt;/script>

&lt;label for="servingFactor">
 Number of people eating: 
&lt;/label>
&lt;input type="number" value='2'
 id="servingFactor" name="servingFactor" min="1">
&lt;h3 id="waffle-batter">Waffle batter&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">1/2&lt;/span> stick butter&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">2&lt;/span> eggs&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">1&lt;/span> pinch salt&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">1/4&lt;/span> cup sugar&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">3/4&lt;/span> cup oats&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">3/4&lt;/span> cup flour&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;span class="unit">1&lt;/span> cup milk (to right consistency)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="mandated-toppings">Mandated toppings&lt;/h3>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Mixed frozen berries compote (no cherries), made by microwaving in a bowl for 3-4 minutes&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Maple syrup&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Powdered sugar&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="instructions">Instructions&lt;/h2>
&lt;h3 id="using-a-high-powered-blender">Using a high powered blender&lt;/h3>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>To make the batter combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until consistent&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h3 id="using-a-shitty-blender-or-making-a-larger-recipe">Using a shitty blender or making a larger recipe&lt;/h3>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Cut the butter into pieces, combine with eggs, sugar, and salt in the blender and blend until consistent&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Add 1/4 cup flour, 1/4 cup oats, and 1/3 cup milk at a time, blend until consistent each time&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;h2 id="pictures">Pictures&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="../images/waffles_1.webp" alt="Waffles">
&lt;img src="../images/waffles_2.webp" alt="Waffles">&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>